<b><font color="#0D4D9B">Deadline: December 10, 1999</font></b><br>



We Want to Highlight Your Newest Workstyle Products<br>
<br>
Do you have a totally cool new workstyle product to enter in Innovations that can't make the Oct. 6 deadline?  Or perhaps you'd like your new product to be judged live on-site at the 2000 International CES?  If the answer is yes, you may want to consider entering your product in our new Workstyle competition.<br>
<br>
As the first awards program to ever showcase the best in workstyle products, the CES Workstyle Awards Program is an excellent opportunity to get your product more media attention and recognition.<br>
<br>
Workstyle products include: notebook computers, wireless information and telecommunications devices, hand-held devices (PDAs), mobile/portable Internet access devices, hand-held navigational equipment and portable peripherals.<br>
<br>
Entries will be judged by top journalists on the product's usefulness, appearance, portability and functionality.<br>
<br>
The winning entries will be presented at a show press conference on Friday, Jan. 7, and will receive an awards plaque to display in their booth.<br>
<br>
Look for program details and online application in the near future. Questions?  Contact Cia Morey at <a href=mailto"cmorey@eia.org">cmorey@eia.org</a>.



		
